thread.title: Concussion that killed teen football player wasn't his first
thread.title_full: Concussion that killed teen football player wasn't his first - seattlepi.com

author: seattlepi.com
title: Concussion that killed teen football player wasn't his first
text:
SEATTLE (AP) â€” A Washington school district has revealed that a football player who died following a head injury had suffered a concussion before.
KCPQ-TV reports ( http://bit.ly/1FWtPdd ) that Highline School District Superintendent Susan Enfield said Thursday morning that Evergreen High School football player Kenney Bui had a concussion several weeks before being injured at last Friday's game.
She says he was cleared by a doctor to return to the field.
The 17-year-old died Monday. He had collapsed during a last week's football game against Highline High School .
The King County Medical Examiner's Office says Bui died from blunt-force trauma to the head.
Highline Public Schools spokeswoman Catherine Carbone Rogers says Bui received surgery at a Seattle hospital and was listed in critical condition Sunday.
Bui was a wide receiver and defensive back.
___
Information from: KCPQ-TV, http://q13fox.com/
